          "author": "Kairui Song",
          "summary": "reviewer mentioned that a systematic test run for one kernel version or config takes about one to two days, and comparing versions/setups takes even longer\n\nReviewer noted that the patch involves mixed writeback, which is a practical case causing a regression, and requested its inclusion for evaluation.\n\nreviewer noted that the current test is focused on writeback and not related to SWAP, suggesting it's better to avoid noise and irrelevant parts by excluding SWAP from the test\n\nThe reviewer provided detailed test results for a fairness evaluation of the mm/mglru patch, including throughput and latency metrics, as well as a fairness index calculated using Jain's fairness metric. The reviewer noted that the current implementation seems fair but requested additional information on why this workload is chosen and its importance for evaluation.\n\nReviewer Kairui Song noted that MGLRU significantly outperforms classical LRU in a test case provided by the CachyOS community, exhibiting lower jitter and better performance, but did not include this information due to concerns about making the cover letter too long.\n\nReviewer noted that since the kernel source code is on tmpfs, it's not a realistic representation of typical usage and suggested testing with source code on disk to better understand I/O noise.",
          "sentiment": "needs_work",
          "sentiment_signals": [
            "lack of urgency",
            "practical consideration",
            "regression",
            "practical case",
            "NEEDS_WORK",
